The paper discusses document retrieval techniques, which is a core topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). However, the focus is on extending these techniques to a broader class of sequence collections, which involves algorithmic aspects related to trees, strings, range queries, and discrete geometry. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer science sub-categories such as data structures (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), databases (cs.DB), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
